+ import { apolloClient } from &#39;@/lib/apollo-client&#39;;
+ import { gql } from &#39;@apollo/client&#39;;

+ /**
+  * GraphQL service layer for Hasura GraphQL API
+  * 
+  * This service provides helper functions for common GraphQL operations.
+  * Use Apollo Client hooks (useQuery, useMutation) in React components for reactive data fetching.
+  * Use these functions for imperative queries or server-side operations.
+  */
+ 
+ /**
+  * Execute a GraphQL query
+  */
+ export async function executeQuery&lt;T = any&gt;(
+   query: string,
+   variables?: Record&lt;string, any&gt;
+ ): Promise&lt;T&gt; {
+   try {
+     const { data, errors } = await apolloClient.query({
+       query: gql(query),
+       variables,
+       fetchPolicy: &#39;network-only&#39;,
+     });
+ 
+     if (errors &amp;&amp; errors.length &gt; 0) {
+       throw new Error(&#96;GraphQL errors: ${errors.map(e =&gt; e.message).join(&#39;, &#39;)}&#96;);
+     }
+ 
+     return data as T;
+   } catch (error) {
+     console.error(&#39;GraphQL query error:&#39;, error);
+     throw error;
+   }
+ }
+ 
+ /**
+  * Execute a GraphQL mutation
+  */
+ export async function executeMutation&lt;T = any&gt;(
+   mutation: string,
+   variables?: Record&lt;string, any&gt;
+ ): Promise&lt;T&gt; {
+   try {
+     const { data, errors } = await apolloClient.mutate({
+       mutation: gql(mutation),
+       variables,
+     });
+ 
+     if (errors &amp;&amp; errors.length &gt; 0) {
+       throw new Error(&#96;GraphQL errors: ${errors.map(e =&gt; e.message).join(&#39;, &#39;)}&#96;);
+     }
+ 
+     return data as T;
+   } catch (error) {
+     console.error(&#39;GraphQL mutation error:&#39;, error);
+     throw error;
+   }
+ }
+ 
+ /**
+  * Example query: Get players
+  * This is a template that can be customized based on your needs
+  */
+ export const GET_PLAYERS_QUERY = gql&#96;
+   query GetPlayers($limit: Int, $offset: Int) {
+     players(limit: $limit, offset: $offset) {
+       id
+       gamertag
+       position
+       currentTeamName
+       created_at
+     }
+   }
+ &#96;;
+ 
+ /**
+  * Example query: Get draft picks
+  */
+ export const GET_DRAFT_PICKS_QUERY = gql&#96;
+   query GetDraftPicks($limit: Int, $offset: Int) {
+     draft_picks(limit: $limit, offset: $offset, order_by: { pick_number: asc }) {
+       id
+       pick_number
+       player_id
+       team_id
+       created_at
+     }
+   }
+ &#96;;
+ 
+ /**
+  * Example query: Get draft pool
+  */
+ export const GET_DRAFT_POOL_QUERY = gql&#96;
+   query GetDraftPool($league_id: uuid) {
+     draft_pool(where: { league_id: { _eq: $league_id }, status: { _eq: &quot;available&quot; } }) {
+       id
+       player_id
+       league_id
+       status

+         id

+       }

The build fails because Clerk requires the publishable key during build. I've:

1. **Updated the layout** to explicitly pass the Clerk publishable key
2. **Updated the README** to document the required environment variable

**To fix the Railway build**, add the following environment variable in your Railway project settings:

- `NEXT_PUBLIC_CLERK_PUBLISHABLE_KEY` - Your Clerk publishable key (get it from https://dashboard.clerk.com/last-active?path=api-keys)

After adding this variable in Railway, the build should succeed. Clerk needs this key during static page generation, so it must be available at build time.

The updated `ClerkProvider` in the layout now explicitly uses the environment variable, which should help with the build process once the variable is set in Railway.
